<h1 id="install-ruby-and-use-gem-to-install-jekyll-centos8">Install ruby and use gem to install jekyll (Centos8)</h1>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="c1"># Login as root</span>
<span class="n">yum</span> <span class="n">install</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">y</span> <span class="n">ruby</span> <span class="n">ruby</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">devel</span> <span class="n">make</span> <span class="n">gcc</span> <span class="n">gcc</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="o">++</span> <span class="n">zlib</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">devel</span> <span class="n">redhat</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">rpm</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">config</span>
<span class="n">gem</span> <span class="n">install</span> <span class="n">jekyll</span> <span class="n">bundler</span></code></pre></figure>

<h1 id="use-jekyll-to-create-a-site-called-blog">Use jekyll to create a site called blog</h1>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="c1"># Login as yourself</span>
<span class="n">jekyll</span> <span class="n">new</span> <span class="n">blog</span></code></pre></figure>

<h1 id="run-website-locally-to-test">Run website locally to test</h1>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="n">cd</span> <span class="n">blog</span>
<span class="n">bundle</span> <span class="nb">exec</span> <span class="n">jekyll</span> <span class="n">serve</span></code></pre></figure>

<h1 id="acess-the-site-on-link-below">Acess the site on link below</h1>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="n">http</span><span class="ss">:/</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mf">127.0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mf">0.1</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">4000</span><span class="o">/</span></code></pre></figure>

<h1 id="create-a-repo-from-githubcom">Create a repo from <a href="https://github.com/trevorqhl/blog">github.com</a></h1>

<h1 id="initialize-and-push-blog-to-github-repo">Initialize and push blog to github repo</h1>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="n">git</span> <span class="n">init</span>
<span class="n">git</span> <span class="n">remote</span> <span class="n">add</span> <span class="n">origin</span> <span class="n">https</span><span class="ss">:/</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">github</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nf">com</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">trevorqhl</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">blog</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nf">git</span>
<span class="n">git</span> <span class="n">add</span> <span class="p">.</span>
<span class="nf">git</span> <span class="n">commit</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">m</span> <span class="s2">"first commit"</span>
<span class="n">git</span> <span class="n">push</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">u</span> <span class="n">origin</span> <span class="n">master</span></code></pre></figure>

<h1 id="update-the-site-and-push-to-github">Update the site and push to github</h1>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="c1"># Once the update is done run website locally to test</span>
<span class="n">bundle</span> <span class="nb">exec</span> <span class="n">jekyll</span> <span class="n">serve</span>

<span class="c1"># Once you are satisfied, check git status</span>
<span class="n">git</span> <span class="n">status</span>

<span class="c1"># If there is new files</span>
<span class="n">git</span> <span class="n">add</span> <span class="o">.</span>

<span class="c1"># commit to local repo</span>
<span class="n">git</span> <span class="n">commit</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">a</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">m</span> <span class="s2">"update blog"</span>

<span class="c1"># push to master</span>
<span class="n">git</span> <span class="n">push</span> </code></pre></figure>

<h1 id="install-with-a-new-theme-jekyllthemesorg">Install with a new theme jekyllthemes.org</h1>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="c1"># Usually you need to do the steps below after clone</span>
<span class="n">bundle</span> <span class="n">init</span>
<span class="n">bundle</span> <span class="n">add</span> <span class="n">jekyll</span>
<span class="n">echo</span> <span class="s1">'gem "jekyll-paginate"'</span> <span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span>  <span class="no">Gemfile</span>
<span class="n">bundle</span> <span class="nb">exec</span> <span class="n">jekyll</span> <span class="n">serve</span></code></pre></figure>

